Not all fruits are equal and neither is when you eat them.
Here’s how to get the most out of your fruits based on what your body needs:

Apple – Your go-to pre-workout fuel or morning energizer
Keeps you full, boosts metabolism, and provides steady energy without a crash.

Pineapple – The ultimate post-meal bloating buster
Packed with bromelain to aid digestion and support gut health.

Kiwi – A gentle post-lunch or post-dinner hero
Helps with digestion, supports immunity, and can even improve sleep quality when eaten at night.

Watermelon – Best as a post-workout refresher or light snack
Hydrating, low in calories, and perfect for hot days or sugar cravings.
